We got a welcome back message, so the table exists.
Next move is to check is there an administrator in it or not...:
Cookie: TrackingId=xlI6B96WIKSgh6Mx' AND (SELECT 'a' FROM users WHERE username='administrator')='a;
We got a welcome back again, so it exists.
The next move is to figure out the password for the administrator. To do this we need burpsuits intruder.
So refresh the page and send the GET request to the intruder.
Change the cookie part like this:
Cookie: TrackingId=xlI6B96WIKSgh6Mx' AND (SELECT SUBSTRING(password,1,1) FROM users WHERE username='administrator')='a; session=UZ3AFmVwjKCVFQKRZ4tGac9X0zZLuUzY
This means it picks the first letter from the password of the administrator and checks if it is the 'a' letter...
So add a payload position marker to the 'a' like this:
WHERE username='administrator')='§a§
In the payload configurations you can add all letters (lowercase, uppercase), and numbers one-by-one.
Next option we have to set is in the payload's settings menu/Grep-match part...clear the list and add: Welcome back! 
That the result what we get, when we have a match, and run the attack.
In my case my first letter in the password is 'r'
To find out the 2nd letter change the SUBSTRING(password,1,1) part to SUBSTRING(password,2,1) and run the attack again. And keep following this method, until there will be no match in the welcome back part.
So my password is:
rodz8ixn9vdaau13x65r  >>>and thats it at SUBSTRING(password,21,1) i didn't got any welcome back response...all we have to do is login with administrator with this password.

